---
import BaseLayout from '../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';

const breadcrumbSchema = {
  '@context': 'https://schema.org',
  '@type': 'BreadcrumbList',
  itemListElement: [
    { '@type': 'ListItem', position: 1, name: 'Home', item: 'https://ultrazoom.app/' },
    { '@type': 'ListItem', position: 2, name: 'Compare', item: 'https://ultrazoom.app/compare' },
    { '@type': 'ListItem', position: 3, name: 'Best Imagus alternatives', item: 'https://ultrazoom.app/compare/imagus-alternatives' },
  ],
};

const itemListSchema = {
  '@context': 'https://schema.org',
  '@type': 'ItemList',
  itemListElement: [
    { '@type': 'ListItem', position: 1, name: 'Ultra Zoom', url: 'https://ultrazoom.app/' },
    { '@type': 'ListItem', position: 2, name: 'Hover Zoom Plus', url: 'https://ultrazoom.app/compare/hover-zoom-plus' },
    { '@type': 'ListItem', position: 3, name: 'Mage', url: 'https://ultrazoom.app/compare/mage' },
    { '@type': 'ListItem', position: 4, name: 'Thumbnail Zoom Plus', url: 'https://ultrazoom.app/compare/thumbnail-zoom-plus' },
  ],
};
---

<BaseLayout
  title="Best Imagus Alternatives in 2026 — Sieve-Rule Migration Guide"
  description="A side-by-side ranking of every Imagus alternative for Chrome and Firefox — by privacy, active maintenance, sieve-rule support, and feature parity."
  currentPage="compare"
  og={{
    url: 'https://ultrazoom.app/compare/imagus-alternatives',
    title: 'Best Imagus Alternatives in 2026',
    description: 'Every Imagus alternative ranked by privacy, maintenance, and sieve-rule support.',
    image: 'https://ultrazoom.app/og/compare-imagus-alternatives.png',
    imageWidth: 1200,
    imageHeight: 630,
  }}
  jsonLd={[breadcrumbSchema, itemListSchema]}
>
    <main class="main page-content" id="main-content">
        <h1>Best Imagus alternatives in 2026</h1>

        <p class="pricing-intro">Imagus has carried sieve-rule hover zoom for over a decade, but development pace varies and Manifest V3 has been a struggle for the entire family of legacy hover-zoom extensions. If you&rsquo;re looking for an Imagus alternative, here&rsquo;s an honest ranking by privacy, maintenance, MV3 readiness, and how well your sieve workflow carries over.</p>

        <section class="help-section" id="ranking">
            <h2>The shortlist</h2>
            <ol class="help-list">
                <li><strong>Ultra Zoom</strong> &mdash; actively maintained, MV3-native on Chrome and a current Firefox add-on, zero telemetry, on-device AI upscaling. Supports community URL-rules packs (auto-updating weekly) and custom URL rules in Pro for migrating sieves. <a href="/">ultrazoom.app</a></li>
                <li><strong>Hover Zoom Plus</strong> &mdash; the most-installed Hover Zoom fork. No sieve, but covers most popular hosts. <a href="/compare/hover-zoom-plus">Full comparison</a>.</li>
                <li><strong>Mage and other Hover Zoom forks</strong> &mdash; sporadic releases, single maintainer, partial MV3. <a href="/compare/mage">Full comparison</a>.</li>
                <li><strong>Thumbnail Zoom Plus (Firefox)</strong> &mdash; a classic that broke when legacy add-ons retired. <a href="/compare/thumbnail-zoom-plus">Full comparison</a>.</li>
            </ol>
        </section>

        <section class="help-section" id="sieve-migration">
            <h2>What happens to your Imagus sieve</h2>
            <ul class="help-list">
                <li><strong>Most popular hosts:</strong> covered by Ultra Zoom&rsquo;s built-in plugins out of the box &mdash; no rules needed.</li>
                <li><strong>Long-tail hosts:</strong> the community URL-rules pack auto-updates weekly and extends coverage without you writing anything.</li>
                <li><strong>Your custom rules:</strong> Ultra Zoom Pro supports custom URL rules. Most Imagus rules translate directly &mdash; the regex / capture-group pattern is the same shape.</li>
                <li><strong>Heavy sieve users:</strong> if you maintain hundreds of personal rules, expect to spend an hour porting the ones that matter. Plugins replace most rules over time.</li>
            </ul>
        </section>

        <section class="help-section" id="comparison-table">
            <h2>Side-by-side comparison</h2>
            <div class="pricing-compare-wrap">
                <table class="pricing-compare">
                    <thead>
                        <tr>
                            <th scope="col">Feature</th>
                            <th scope="col">Ultra Zoom</th>
                            <th scope="col">Imagus</th>
                            <th scope="col">Hover Zoom Plus</th>
                        </tr>
                    </thead>
                    <tbody>
                        <tr>
                            <th scope="row">Sieve-style URL rules</th>
                            <td>&#10003; (Pro)</td>
                            <td aria-label="Yes">&#10003;</td>
                            <td aria-label="No">&ndash;</td>
                        </tr>
                        <tr>
                            <th scope="row">Auto-updating community rule pack</th>
                            <td aria-label="Yes">&#10003;</td>
                            <td>Manual sieve</td>
                            <td aria-label="No">&ndash;</td>
                        </tr>
                        <tr>
                            <th scope="row">Site-specific plugins</th>
                            <td aria-label="Yes">&#10003;</td>
                            <td>Limited</td>
                            <td aria-label="Yes">&#10003;</td>
                        </tr>
                        <tr>
                            <th scope="row">Theater mode</th>
                            <td aria-label="Yes">&#10003;</td>
                            <td aria-label="Yes">&#10003;</td>
                            <td aria-label="No">&ndash;</td>
                        </tr>
                        <tr>
                            <th scope="row">Reverse image search shortcuts</th>
                            <td aria-label="Yes">&#10003;</td>
                            <td aria-label="Yes">&#10003;</td>
                            <td aria-label="No">&ndash;</td>
                        </tr>
                        <tr>
                            <th scope="row">On-device AI upscaling</th>
                            <td>&#10003; (Pro)</td>
                            <td aria-label="No">&ndash;</td>
                            <td aria-label="No">&ndash;</td>
                        </tr>
                        <tr>
                            <th scope="row">Video preview controls</th>
                            <td>&#10003; (Pro)</td>
                            <td aria-label="No">&ndash;</td>
                            <td aria-label="No">&ndash;</td>
                        </tr>
                        <tr>
                            <th scope="row">Active development</th>
                            <td>Every few weeks</td>
                            <td>Variable</td>
                            <td>Limited</td>
                        </tr>
                        <tr>
                            <th scope="row">Manifest V3 native</th>
                            <td aria-label="Yes">&#10003;</td>
                            <td>Partial</td>
                            <td>Partial</td>
                        </tr>
                        <tr>
                            <th scope="row">Zero telemetry guarantee</th>
                            <td aria-label="Yes">&#10003;</td>
                            <td>Unclear</td>
                            <td>Unclear</td>
                        </tr>
                    </tbody>
                </table>
            </div>
        </section>

        <section class="help-section" id="cta">
            <h2>Try it free</h2>
            <p>The core extension is free forever, with the entire site catalogue and the auto-updating community rule pack. Pro &mdash; including custom URL rules &mdash; is a 7-day free trial when you&rsquo;re ready. <a href="/pricing">See plans</a>.</p>
            <ul class="install-links">
                <li>
                    <a href="https://chromewebstore.google.com/detail/ultra-zoom/jalclpdejbeamaamcpbolkclpnleagmg" class="install-button chrome" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Install for Chrome</a>
                </li>
                <li>
                    <a href="https://addons.mozilla.org/en-US/firefox/addon/ultra-zoom/" class="install-button firefox" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Install for Firefox</a>
                </li>
            </ul>
        </section>
    </main>
</BaseLayout>
